{"TopicId":223551,"ForumId":130,"TopicTitle":"WASD for KSP","CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-07T03:20:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-07T03:20:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the permission of \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/226909-archlinus/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022226909\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/226909-archlinus/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@ArchLinus\u003C/a\u003E, who has left the scene, I have adopted this mod for KSP 2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConverts the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E camera into a WASD fly camera.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpon initial installation the WASD keys will be active\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf not active, then hold down the right mouse:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nWASD moves laterally\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nQ and E move vertically.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nShift/Control speeds up and slows down the camera while held\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWASD mode can be toggled on or off using alt\u002Bw.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EInstallation instructions\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E recommended, will install dependencies\u003Cbr\u003E\nor\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0[Install SpaceWarp](https://spacedock.info/mod/3257/Space%20Warp)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0Extract wasd_for_vab.zip to your KSP folder\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EAvailability\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nLicense: MIT\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nDownload:\u00A0\u00A0https://spacedock.info/mod/3276/WASD For \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSource code:\u00A0\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/linuxgurugamer/WASDForVAB\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/linuxgurugamer/WASDForVAB\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mr.DingALing","CreatedById":195098,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-07T04:41:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow we are going places!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:prograde:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/prograde3.png\u0022 title=\u0022:prograde:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Biggen","CreatedById":173719,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-07T19:31:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E only shows it as compatible with 0.2.0 and not the newest patch (0.2.1).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rogerawong","CreatedById":204910,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-17T22:08:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224365025\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022223551\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221707334302\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173719\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Biggen\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/7/2024 at 1:31 PM, Biggen said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E only shows it as compatible with 0.2.0 and not the newest patch (0.2.1).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis issue seems to have been resolved.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jezzick","CreatedById":175940,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-21T04:15:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks like there is some code in WASDPatches.cs that potentially might add pitch and yaw to the controls? do you think that will be possible or likely?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StellatedCUBE","CreatedById":227483,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-25T06:42:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the release, the BepInEx folder is called \u0022BepinEx\u0022 instead. This breaks all mods on non-Windows machines, and some specifically configured Windows ones too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}